rtsa rgyud kyi le'u bco lnga par chos thams cad rmi lam bzhin du gsungs pa'i don 'grel pa ni bdag byin gyis brlab pa'i rim par gsungs so/ /
so sor rtog pa'i shes rab kyis dpyod tshul yang rtsa rgyud kyi le'u dgu pa'i bshad rgyud dgongs pa lung ston du rgyu las 'bras bu ma brtags par 'byung mod kyang so sor brtags na gang na'ang mi gnas pa'i tshul gyis brtag par gsungs la/ rdo rje 'phreng ba'i le'u bcu drug pa las dus gsum po re re la'ang gsum gsum du rim gyis phye nas dpyod par gsungs so/ /
phyogs mthun gyi thabs rgyud rdo rje snying po rgyan gyi rgyud las kyang gzugs can rnams la rdul gyi phyogs cha'i dpyad pa dang / sems la skad cig ma gsum gsum du phye ba'i dpyad pas stong nyid gtan la 'bebs par gsungs pas/ lta ba'i go ba 'tshol lugs phar phyin gyi theg pa bzhin du bshad do; ;

Candrakīrti’s Illuminating Lamp teaches that from the sequential dissolution of earth, water, fire, winds, and consciousness, the four signs from mirage-like to flame will appear. It has already been explained that when the winds have dissolved, the first appearance arises. Therefore the descriptions of many signs, including the above, arising at the time of the three appearances make no sense. [231] Rather, follow Clear Compilation of the Five Stages, which, like the Compendium of Practice, asserts:
First, with five rays of light,
a mirage-like experience appears;
second, a moonlike appearance;
third, a permeation of sunlight;
and from the appearance of night, close-to-attainment.[711]
The mention of mirage without the other three is just an abbreviation. Extensive descriptions can be found in the Later Tantra and in Illuminating Lamp wherever this topic appears.
In summary, the individual traditions described above have not added any new objects of focus, such as syllables, in this section on mind isolation.[712] However, having first practiced body isolation, and without analyzing, in general, how many of the four empty states speech-isolation vajra repetition can or cannot induce, it is not good to add new objects of focus as methods for inducing mind isolation because this would be to cast aside the practice of penetrating the vital points of the inner body as the principal method of inducing mind isolation and to teach some minor methods instead.
The objects of focus found in the core teachings passed on from Naktso as methods for developing bliss and the teachings on their five divisions are given because of the recognized need to develop bliss quickly, but I do not see them as representing the texts.

rtsa rgyud kyi le'u lnga pa dang / bdun pa'i mtshan gyi skabs su/ rim pa bzhin kun tu spyod pa mchog dang / sngags spyod pa mchog ces gsungs pa'i don sgron gsal las/ rang gzhan gyi don kun sgrub pa'i spyod pa phul du byung ba dang / sngags zlos pa po'i spyod pa gsum la bshad do/ /
snga ma yang spyod pa gsum gyi spyi ming ngo ; ;
le'u dgu pa las/ byang sems dang de bzhin gshegs pa'i spyod pa gnyis gsungs pa'i don sgron gsal las/ 'jig rten dang 'gal lam mi 'gal yang rung / gang dang gang gis sems can gyi don rdzogs par 'gyur ba'i rnam pa de dang des/ sngags pa rnams ci nus par rab tu 'jug pa ni dang po dang / rin po che lta bu'i sngags pas rdzogs rim rtogs nas mnyam par ma bzhag pa'i sbyor ba'i spyod pas tshe 'di nyid la rang gi ngo bo brje ba'i spyod pa ni gnyis par bshad do/ /
de'i dang po ni byang sems kyi spyod pa spyi dang / gnyis pa ni rdzogs rim la gsungs pa ni mtshon pa tsam dang / rin po che lta bu'i gang zag ni gtso bo yin pa la dgongs pas/ bla med kyi 'dod yon la spyod pa'i spyod pa khyad par can thams cad do; ;
